AdSense &amp; YouTube monetization</li><li>YouTube SEO</li><li>Email Marketing/Mailchimp</li><li>Landing Page for Email Marketing</li></ul><p><br>&nbsp;</p></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class 16</strong></td><td><ul><li>Overall Overview</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class 17</strong></td><td><ul><li>Market-Place Introduction and Analysis (Fiverr, Upwork)</li><li>LinkedIn Market Job Analysis</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class 18</strong></td><td><ul><li><strong>Fiverr Account Creation</strong></li><li>Gig Creation</li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class 19</strong></td><td><ul><li><strong>Job Application (Tricks)</strong></li></ul></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class 20</strong></td><td><ul><li>Payoneer Account Creation</li><li><strong>Over-all questions answer</strong></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p><br>&nbsp;</p>","created_at":"2022-03-11T07:18:23.000000Z","updated_at":"2022-08-24T07:23:22.000000Z","user":{"id":120,"name":"Asaf ud Dulla","email":"kakon53212@gmail.com","username":"Asaf_Kakon","phone_number":"01985541747","profile_picture":"images/pp/1647193970_Asaf ud Dulla120.jpg","slug":null,"affiliate_link":null,"facebook":"https://www.linkedin.com/in/asaf-ud-dulla-478908187","linkedin":"https://www.facebook.com/asafuddoulla.kakon.9","applied":1,"designation":null,"experties":"Digital Marketing","about_me":null,"cv":null,"note":null,"user_id":null,"email_verified_at":null,"created_at":"2022-03-09T06:55:55.000000Z","updated_at":"2022-06-25T14:19:05.000000Z","fb_id":null,"google_id":null},"category":{"id":6,"name":"Marketing","icon":null,"created_at":"2022-01-08T05:53:27.000000Z","updated_at":"2022-01-08T05:53:27.000000Z"}},{"id":15,"name":"Image Processing in Python","thumbnail":"images/frontimages/courses/1647370943_Image_Processing_in_Python15.png","user_id":36,"category_id":3,"price":"3000.00","old_price":"6000.00","status":"approved","time_duration":"24","media_link":null,"rating_number":"1","rating_quantity":"5","number_of_lessons":1,"student_enrolled":null,"discount":50,"timing":"9.00 PM","venu":"Online","description":"<p>Class 1 Introduction of Image processing 1. What is image processing 2. Why we need it 3. How it works 4. Real life impact of image processing 5. Examples Class 2 Installation and Setup 1. Install opencv, python 3 2. Set up the environment Class 3 Conversion of Images 1. Finding image details 2. Splitting an Image into Individual Channels 3. Grayscale Images 4. Image Thresholding Class 4 Image Sampling 1. Image sub sampling 2. Down sampling Class 5 Image quantization Class 4 Resizing Image 1. Rotate images 2. Crop images and so on Class 5 Image Aliasing 1. Spatial aliasing 2. Anti-aliasing Class 6 Image enhancement part1 Class 7 Image enhancement part2 Class 8 Accessing the Camera Class 9 Read and Write videos Class 10 Image Filtering Class 11 Image Features Detect the features of images. Class 12 Image Alignment Class 13 Image Stitching and Creating Panoramas 1. Stitching the images 2. Creating panoramas Class 14 Remove the noise Removing the noise of images Class 15 High Dynamic Range Imaging (HDR) Class 16 Object tracking and Detection</p>","requirments":"<p>Basic knowledge of object oriented programming language.</p>","forwho":"<p>Any interested learner can join this course.</p>","what_will_learn":"<p>Some noteworthy mentions: Machine Learning, deep learning, Nlp, Image processing, Web Scrapping, Data mining, patter Recognition, Dart, Flutter, python, C, PHP, bootstrap, Web development, Kubernetes, Docker, SQL, Graphics, OpenCV, Networking, Active Learning, Linear Algebra, Statistics, Association Rule mining, Data Science.&nbsp;</p>","created_at":"2022-03-15T18:15:27.000000Z","updated_at":"2022-07-13T12:59:38.000000Z","user":{"id":36,"name":"Lamima Tabassum Ava","email":"lamima7777@gmail.com","username":"Ava#7i","phone_number":"01790507520","profile_picture":"images/avatar.svg","slug":null,"affiliate_link":null,"facebook":"https://www.facebook.com/","linkedin":"https://www.linkedin.com/","applied":1,"designation":null,"experties":"image processing","about_me":null,"cv":null,"note":null,"user_id":null,"email_verified_at":null,"created_at":"2022-02-22T19:53:06.000000Z","updated_at":"2022-02-22T20:49:04.000000Z","fb_id":null,"google_id":null},"category":{"id":3,"name":"Programming","icon":null,"created_at":"2022-01-08T05:53:27.000000Z","updated_at":"2022-01-08T05:53:27.000000Z"}},{"id":16,"name":"Graphic Design","thumbnail":"images/frontimages/courses/1655278700_Graphic_Design.jpg","user_id":35,"category_id":2,"price":"1999.80","old_price":"9999.00","status":"approved","time_duration":"40","media_link":null,"rating_number":"1","rating_quantity":"5","number_of_lessons":1,"student_enrolled":null,"discount":80,"timing":"9 PM","venu":"Online","description":"<p><strong>In this graphic design course we will learn about raster and vector based graphic design. Ex. Logo Design, Banner Design, Business Card Design, Branding Design etc. The software we will use, Adobe Photoshop and Adobe Illustrator.</strong></p><p>&nbsp;</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Topic</strong></td><td><strong>Total Class</strong></td><td><strong>Topics</strong></td><td><strong>Total Time</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Adobe Photoshop</td><td>10</td><td>Introduction about Adobe Photoshop. Discuss raster design and learn to use Adobe Photoshop</td><td>20 Hours</td></tr><tr><td>Adobe Illustrator</td><td>10</td><td>Introduction about Adobe Illustrator. Discuss vector design and learn to use Adobe Illustrator.</td><td>20 Hours</td></tr><tr><td>Exam and&nbsp;Guideline for Marketplace</td><td>03</td><td>Written and Viva Exam. Submit Project. Guideline for Marketplace.</td><td>5+ Hours.</td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Adobe Photoshop Class Module</strong></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Class # 01</strong></td><td><ol><li>Introduction with Photoshop</li><li>Document Setup</li><li>Interface Overview</li><li>Screen Mode</li><li>Zoom in and out</li><li>Documentation Pan</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 02</strong></td><td><ol><li>Color Apply</li><li>Selection Basic</li><li>Layer Basic</li><li>Undo &amp; Redo</li><li>Document Save</li><li>Selection Tool</li><li>Sub Selection</li><li>Feather</li><li>Anti-Alias</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 03</strong></td><td><ol><li>Crop Tool</li><li>Image Size</li><li>Save for Web</li><li>File Format</li><li>Brush Tool</li><li>Create New Brush</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 04</strong></td><td><ol><li>Spot Healing, Patch Tool</li><li>Content-Aware Move, Red Eye Tool</li><li>Clone Stamp, Pattern Stamp Tool</li><li>Blur, Sharpen and Smudge Tool</li><li>Dodge, Burn and Sponge Tool</li><li>History Brush Tool</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 05</strong></td><td><ol><li>Pen Tool (Path Mode, Shape Mode)</li><li>Path Selection Tool</li><li>Direct Selection Tool</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 06</strong></td><td><ol><li>Gradient Tool</li><li>Paint Bucket Tool</li><li>Type Tool</li><li>Character Palette</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 07</strong></td><td><ol><li>Eraser Tool</li><li>Layer Lock</li><li>Layer Merge</li><li>Layer Mode</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 8</strong></td><td><ol><li>Group and Ungroup</li><li>Opacity and Fill</li><li>Layer Masking</li><li>Clipping Mask</li><li>Blending Tool</li><li>Wooden Box</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 9</strong></td><td><ol><li>Fundamentals of Advertisement</li><li>Menu Details</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 10</strong></td><td><ol><li>Logo Design&nbsp;</li><li>Business Card Design</li><li>Banner Design</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 11</strong></td><td><ol><li>Exam and Guideline for Marketplace</li></ol></td></tr></tbody></table></figure><p>&nbsp;</p><h4><strong>Adobe Illustrator Class Module</strong></h4><p>&nbsp;</p><figure class=\"table\"><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Class # 01</strong></td><td><ol><li>Introducing Illustrator</li><li>Using the Welcome Screen</li><li>Introducing Vector Graphics</li><li>Introducing Illustrator Interface, Tool Bar and Setting New Document</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 02</strong></td><td><ol><li>Object / Shape Creation using Basic Shapes and Pen Tool</li><li>Selection Basics</li><li>Introducing Anchor Points</li><li>Introducing Fill and Stroke and Applying Color</li><li>Object Arrangement and Working with Object Grouping, Locking and Hiding</li><li>Using Undo/Redo, Guide, Grid and Saving a Document</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 03</strong></td><td><ol><li>An overview of the Color Palette</li><li>Black vs Rich Black</li><li>Working with Swatches</li><li>Introducing Illustrator Gradient and applying in Object</li><li>Using Swatches for Gradient</li><li>Creating and saving new Gradient Swatches</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 04</strong></td><td><ol><li>Introducing Object Transformations and working with Scales, Rotate and free Transform Tool</li><li>Duplicating Objects and Transform again&nbsp;</li><li>Moving Objects in Increments&nbsp;</li><li>Using Offset Path dialogue box</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 05</strong></td><td><ol><li>Drawing with Pen Tool</li><li>Modifying&nbsp; a path and understanding open and close path</li><li>Making use of the join command</li><li>Modifying and converting Anchor Points</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 06</strong></td><td><ol><li>Introducing Eraser, Scissors and Knife Tools</li><li>Width, Wrap, Twirl, Pucker etc.</li><li>Share Tool and Reshape Tool</li><li>An overview of stroke and stroke palette</li><li>Stroke cap, Stroke join and stroke dash &amp; gap</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 07</strong></td><td><ol><li>Pathfinder</li><li>Blend and Masks</li><li>Type Tool</li><li>Character Palette</li><li>Paragraph Palette</li><li>Type Menu Details</li><li>Text Wrap</li></ol></td></tr><tr><td><strong>Class # 08</stro